The paper deals with algorithms for finding out-trees and out-branchings in directed graphs, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The paper uses techniques from randomized and deterministic algorithms, and the analysis involves combinatorial and probabilistic arguments. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
